  "body_text": null,
  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\totally.ordered{X}]\nStates:\nwhen:\n. X is \\set\nthat:\n. allOf:\n  . \\partially.ordered{X}\n  . forAll: a, b is \\set\n    where:\n    . a \"in\" X\n    . b \"in\" X\n    then:\n    . anyOf:\n      . a \\:precedes:/ b\n      . b \\:precedes:/ a\nDocumented:\n. called: \"totally ordered\"\n. written: \"X? \\text{ is totally ordered}\"\n. description: \"A partially ordered set $X$ is totally ordered, or a chain, when every two elements are comparable: $a \\preceq b$ or $b \\preceq a$ for all $a, b \\in X$.\"\nId: \"0ef588f7-e574-42c7-9c95-f2fa289db366\"",
